      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/sqa-mrl5",
      "rationale": "At MRL 5 the required SQA gradation is 4, demanding formal configuration management, independent code review, and documented regression testing. The CFD solver (OpenFOAM fork) has version control and a test suite, but independent code review was not performed and regression coverage is limited to 40% of hemolysis-relevant code paths. Achieved gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/code-verification-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Required gradation 4 demands manufactured-solution verification across the full hemolysis constitutive model. Only Couette-flow and pipe-flow manufactured solutions were exercised; the power-law hemolysis accumulation term was not independently verified. Achieved gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/discretization-mrl5",
      "rationale": "A three-level Richardson extrapolation was performed; GCI values on hemolysis index reach 12% on the finest mesh, exceeding the 5% threshold required at gradation 4. Spatial convergence is demonstrated for pressure and velocity but not for the hemolysis scalar transport equation at all five operating points. Achieved gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/test-conditions-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (blood analog viscosity, temperature, hematocrit) were partially characterized. Hematocrit was reported as a nominal range (35–45%) rather than a measured per-sample value, preventing precise boundary-condition matching. Required gradation 3 demands fully characterized and matched boundary conditions. Achieved gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/output-comparison-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Predicted hemolysis index (MIH) was compared against experimental measurements at three of five operating points; two high-flow conditions were excluded due to experimental scatter exceeding 30%. Quantitative agreement metrics (U_num, U_exp) were computed but the validation comparison metric does not satisfy the area validation metric required at gradation 4. Achieved gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is directly relevant to the clinical endpoint. However, sub-lethal platelet activation, a secondary safety QoI at MRL 5, was not modeled. Gradation 4 requires all safety-relevant QoIs to be addressed. Achieved gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic pump geometry under controlled lab conditions. The COU requires prediction for a specific commercial VAD geometry under in-vivo-representative pulsatile inflow; the gap in geometry and inflow conditions constitutes a significant relevance deficit. Achieved gradation 2 against a required gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/solver-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence studies and floating-point sensitivity analyses required at gradation 4 were not performed. Solver residuals were monitored but no formal solver error budget was constructed. Flagged as an epistemic gap at MRL 5; achieved gradation 1 by default."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/use-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "No formal user-qualification protocol or independent simulation replication was conducted. Gradation 3 requires documented analyst qualification and at least one independent replication of the simulation setup. Neither was performed. Flagged as epistemic gap; achieved gradation 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/model-form-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Model-form uncertainty for the power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients) was not quantified. Alternative constitutive models (Faghih-Sharp, Arwatz-Bhatt) were not evaluated. Required gradation 4 demands comparative model-form assessment. Flagged as epistemic gap; achieved gradation 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/model-inputs-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Input uncertainty characterization for blood rheological parameters (yield stress, shear-thinning index) was limited to nominal literature values. Monte Carlo UQ was performed on geometric tolerances only; rheological parameter distributions were not propagated. Required gradation 4 demands full input uncertainty propagation. Flagged as epistemic gap; achieved gradation 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/test-samples-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis data were drawn from a single laboratory source with a single blood lot. Gradation 3 requires multi-source or multi-lot experimental data to characterize biological variability. No inter-laboratory or inter-lot comparison was available. Flagged as epistemic gap; achieved gradation 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/input-equivalency-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Equivalency between simulation input parameters and experimental test article parameters was not formally demonstrated. Pump clearance gaps, surface roughness, and impeller blade angles were taken from nominal CAD; as-built measurements were unavailable. Gradation 3 requires documented equivalency verification. Flagged as epistemic gap; achieved gradation 1."
